'''Middletown High School''' is a public [[high school]] in [[Middletown, Ohio]].  It is the only public high school in the Middletown City School District.

==[[Ohio High School Athletic Association]] State Championships==
* Boys [[Basketball]] <U+2013> 1944, 1946, 1947, 1952, 1953, 1956, 1957 <ref name="Yappi Basketball AAA">{{cite web|url=http://www.yappi.com/boysbasketball/AAA.html|title=Yappi Sports Basketball AAA|accessdate=2007-02-12|author=Yappi}}</ref>
* Boys [[Cross Country Running|Cross Country]] <U+2013> 2004 <ref name="Ohio High School Athletic Association">{{cite web|url=http://www.ohsaa.org/|title=Ohio High School Athletic Association Web site|accessdate=2006-12-31|author=[[OHSAA]]}}</ref>
* Boys [[Athletics (track and field)|Track and Field]] <U+2013> 2002 <ref name="Ohio High School Athletic Association">{{cite web|url=http://www.ohsaa.org/|title=Ohio High School Athletic Association Web site|accessdate=2006-12-31|author=[[OHSAA]]}}</ref>

==Notable Alumni==
* [[Todd Bell]]&nbsp;&ndash; [[Pro Bowl]] [[Safety (football position)|safety]] in the [[NFL]] during the  1980s[http://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/BellTo00.htm]
* [[Butch Carter]]&nbsp;&ndash; Former player and Head Coach in the [[National Basketball Association]], brother of [[Cris Carter]]
* [[Cris Carter]]&nbsp;&ndash; Former [[NFL]] Pro-Bowl and All-Decade player and analyst, likely first ballot hall of fame inductee, brother of [[Butch Carter]][http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NFL_1990s_All-Decade_Team]
* [[Jerry Lucas]]&nbsp;&ndash; Legendary [[National Basketball Association|NBA]] [[Basketball Hall of Fame|Hall of Famer]], [[NBA]] champion, Olympic gold medalist, author, and world-renowned memory education expert. Later named one of the NBA's 50 greatest players[http://www.nba.com/history/players/50greatest.html]
* [[Clarence Page]]&nbsp;&ndash; [[Pulitzer Prize]] winner, [[journalist]], [[syndicated columnist]] and member of the [[editorial board]] for the [[Chicago Tribune]]

